Subject: [liste-egc] Post-doctoral position in Biostatistics/Statistics

Post-doctoral fellow in Biostatistics/Statistics


Employer: Institute of Cardiometabolism and Nutrition (ICAN)

Location: Paris, France

Compensation: 50 000 ? - 40 000 ? net (depends on skills and experience)

Job Type : Contract

Term of Position: 24 months

Posted: January 1, 2015

Application Deadline : Open until filled


Description:

Excellent opportunity to work in a leading scientific institution with  
dedicated professionals

Offering career and professional support

Join ICAN & l'Université de Pierre et Marie Curie - France's premier  
clinical, science and research institutions


We are seeking to appoint a motivated Postdoctoral fellow to work as  
part of a interdisciplinary multi-European country study on  
Metagenomics in Cardiometabolic Diseases (METACARDIS) to help analyze  
and combine clinical, lifestyle and ?omics? data that is generated.
The METACARDIS study is dedicated to the relationship between gut  
microbiota and cardiometabolic diseases and the comorbidities,  
including obesity, diabetes and heart diseases at different disease  
stages.
You will provide statistical input to a multidisciplinary team working  
to understand the clinical, lifestyle and gene expression factors  
influencing the gut microbiota.


  Requirements. Ideal applicant should have:

1.     PhD degree in biostatistics, statistics or related fields.

2.     Strong quantitative background in data bioclinical data  
analysis for and ?omics? of various nature. Experience with  
measurement error, diagnostic testing, causal inference, and  
longitudinal data analysis is preferred.

3.    Interest in biology.

4.  Good spoken and written English, excellent communication skills,  
mature and motivated, as well as a pro-active attitude, creative and  
multitasking.




To apply:

Applicants are asked a send a cover letter describing your research  
interests and interest in the position, CV, and three references  
(including name and contact information) to Nataliya Sokolovska  
nataliya.sokolovska@upmc.fr with subject line ?Postdoc application?.


Employer:

ICAN is new institute dedicated to research, care and training in  
cardiometabolic disease. ICAN is linked to research bodies INSERM and
Pierre & Marie Curie University (UPMC) which is one of the largest  
universities teaching science and medicine in France and in Europe,  
with 4000 researchers and teaching academics/researchers, 180  
laboratories, and some 30 000 students including 8000 in postgraduate  
studies. UPMC is based in the Latin Quarter in Paris, with most  
facilities on a campus of 500 000m².
ICAN is associated with 2 medical faculty in Paris teaching hospitals  
[CHUs]: Saint-Antoine and Pitié-Salpêtrière. Partnerships with a  
number of hospitals and health care centers.



